OL,6,FShe sentenced Alan Forsythe, of
OL,7,FArmistead Court, Fleetwood, to 15
OL,8,Fweeks in jail to run consecutively to
OL,9,Fthe sentence he is currently serving.
OL,11,FHowever, she said she considered the
OL,12,Fchildren's right to a family life when
OL,13,Fsentencing Mrs Forsythe.
OL,15,F"You knew it was a criminal offence,"
OL,16,Fshe told the mother. "You have a
OL,17,Fprevious conviction and you went on to
OL,18,Fcommit this offence over this period.
OL,19,FThis was fraudulent activity over a
OL,20,Fsustained period of 36 months that you
OL,21,Fwere defrauding the DWP.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/12
